0. ONE-LINE SUMMARY
================================================================================

You can USE datatree for your own coding, writing, research, and knowledge
work — as many times as you want, on as many of your own machines as you
want, individually or with your own team. You cannot SELL it, HOST it as a
paid service, REPACKAGE it as a competing MCP/plugin/product, or USE IT TO
TRAIN any AI model.

================================================================================
1. DEFINITIONS
================================================================================

  "Software" means the datatree project, including its source code,
  compiled binaries, schemas, prompts, plugin manifests, install scripts,
  design documents, bundled models, and any files in the official
  repository at https://github.com/omanishay-cyber/datatree (and its
  future canonical home).

  "You" means the individual or legal entity exercising rights under this
  license.

  "Licensor" means Anish Trivedi, the copyright holder.

  "Production Use" means running the Software for your own coding,
  debugging, writing, research, notes, learning, documentation, or
  knowledge work — whether on your personal computer, a computer you own
  at your workplace, or a machine under your day-to-day control. Both
  commercial employment and personal projects count as Production Use and
  are freely permitted.

  "Hosted Service" means making the Software, or any substantial portion
  of its functionality, available to third parties as a managed service
  — whether paid, freemium, ad-supported, or free — where those third
  parties do not install the Software themselves.

  "Derivative MCP Product" means any software you publish, distribute,
  or offer to third parties whose primary value proposition overlaps
  substantially with the Software (e.g., another "persistent AI memory
  MCP", "AI superbrain", "Claude context manager", or similar), and which
  was built using the Software's source code, schemas, design documents,
  prompts, or compiled artefacts.

================================================================================
2. WHAT YOU ARE FREE TO DO
================================================================================

Subject to your compliance with Section 3 (restrictions), the Licensor
grants you a worldwide, royalty-free, non-exclusive, non-transferable
license to:

  (a)  INSTALL AND RUN the Software on any computer you personally own or
       personally operate, as many times as you wish, for as long as you
       wish. This includes laptops, desktops, servers, virtual machines,
       and containers.

  (b)  USE the Software for Production Use — coding, debugging, writing,
       blogging, research, note-taking, studying, learning, preparing
       documents, managing personal or team knowledge, or any similar
       productive work — including when that work is performed for pay or
       as part of a commercial job. You do not need to pay anyone to run
       datatree as part of your day job.

  (c)  MODIFY the Software locally for your own use. You can tweak
       settings, write custom MCP tools, add scanners, adjust prompts,
       and integrate datatree into your personal or team workflow.

  (d)  SHARE the Software with members of your own team or household
       (defined as people who share a physical residence, are employed by
       the same legal entity as you, or are direct collaborators on your
       project). Every such person must still comply with this license.

  (e)  LEARN from the Software's source code and design documents.
       Reading the code to understand how datatree works, for your own
       education or for non-commercial teaching, is explicitly allowed.

  (f)  SUBMIT BUG REPORTS, feature requests, and pull requests back to
       the upstream repository. Contributions accepted upstream remain
       under this license.

  (g)  SCREENSHOT, RECORD, OR DEMO the Software in blog posts, talks,
       tutorials, or videos — attribution to "datatree by Anish
       Trivedi" appreciated.

================================================================================
3. WHAT YOU MAY NOT DO
================================================================================

You may NOT, without a separate written agreement signed by the Licensor:

  (a)  SELL the Software, in whole or in part. This includes: selling
       copies, selling access, selling installations, selling bundled
       support as the primary purpose, selling hardware whose primary
       value is running datatree, or charging any fee whose provision
       relies on the Software's functionality.

  (b)  OFFER THE SOFTWARE AS A HOSTED SERVICE (see §1). You cannot spin
       up a SaaS, a managed API, a hosted "datatree cloud", a public
       multi-tenant instance, or any similar offering where third parties
       use datatree without installing it themselves.

  (c)  PUBLISH A DERIVATIVE MCP PRODUCT (see §1). You cannot take the
       Software's source code, schemas, prompts, or design and use them
       as the foundation for your own published AI-memory MCP, AI
       superbrain, AI context manager, AI plugin, or similar tool and
       distribute that tool to others. This includes open-source
       releases: you cannot publish a competitor even for free.

  (d)  REPACKAGE OR REBRAND the Software and distribute it as your own.
       Removing "datatree", renaming the project, claiming authorship,
       or shipping a fork under a different brand is not allowed.

  (e)  USE THE SOFTWARE TO TRAIN OR FINE-TUNE any machine-learning model,
       language model, embedding model, agent framework, or AI system,
       whether for research or commercial purposes. This includes using
       the source code, the architectural design, the prompts, the
       schemas, or any derived outputs as training data.

  (f)  REMOVE OR OBSCURE copyright notices, license files, branding,
       version strings, or the markers datatree injects into your
       CLAUDE.md / AGENTS.md / GEMINI.md / plugin manifests.

  (g)  GRANT SUBLICENSES. Your right to use the Software cannot be
       passed to anyone else. Each user must install their own copy and
       accept this license directly.

  (h)  SUE THE LICENSOR for patent infringement related to the Software
       and expect to keep your license. If you bring such a suit, your
       rights under Section 2 terminate immediately.

================================================================================
4. THIRD-PARTY COMPONENTS
================================================================================

datatree statically links, dynamically references, and bundles a number of
third-party open-source components (Rust crates, Tree-sitter grammars, the
Bun runtime, the Python runtime, ONNX Runtime components, Tesseract OCR,
FFmpeg, etc.). Each such component remains licensed under its own original
license (MIT, Apache-2.0, BSD, etc.). Nothing in this license weakens,
supersedes, or alters the terms of those upstream licenses.

This license governs the datatree-original work only — the integration
glue, the plugin manifests, the install scripts, the vision app, the
scanners, the brain logic, the design documents, the 27-layer schema, and
all other material produced by the datatree project itself.

